Chat

Create Chat Agent Configurations

Chat agent configurations define the functionality that’s available to your agents and support supervisors. Create configurations to give different capabilities to multiple types of users.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Performance Editions, Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To create and edit configurations: Customize Application

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. Migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

Chat agent configurations enable you to control your users’ access to certain Chat features. Create multiple configurations and assign them to different types of users.

From Setup, enter Chat Agent Configurations in the Quick Find box, then select Chat Agent Configurations.
Click New.
Choose the settings for your Chat agent configuration.
Click Save.

Create and Assign Chat Skills
Create Chat Deployments
